columns.name: balance_after_usd
columns.description: Balance of Wallet Account at creation (Always set to 0.00)

columns.name: currency_type
columns.description: Type of currency of transaction or Account

columns.name: inserted_at_ts
columns.description: Timestamp that indicates the time the record was inserted into the model by dbt.

columns.name: ledger_account_id
columns.description: Unique identifier for customers wallet account. Can be joined onto `credit_id` or `debit_id` in ledger line

columns.name: ledger_account_type
columns.description: Denotes the type of ledger movement e.g was it user or system generated

columns.name: location_code
columns.description: The geographical location. It can be at a regional level (for example, 'ny') or for all of FanDuel (i.e. 'all')

columns.name: product_name
columns.description: The FanDuel product affiliated with the transaction. Examples include “dfs”, “sb”, “casino”, and “racing”, etc. Source platform provides a unique ID which represents the product and through a lookup to fdg_product, this field is mapped to a user-readable value that appears in the table.

columns.name: sns_message_timestamp
columns.description: Timestamp when the streamed sns message was received.

columns.name: stg__inserted_at_ts
columns.description: Timestamp that indicates the time the record was inserted by dbt into the staging model used as a source.

columns.name: stg__updated_at_ts
columns.description: Timestamp that indicates the last time the records was updated by dbt in the staging model used as a source.

columns.name: unique_key
columns.description: A composite primary key generated for the table using a combination of fields.

columns.name: updated_at_ts
columns.description: Timestamp that indicates the time the record was last updated in the model by dbt.

columns.name: wallet_reference
columns.description: This field will contain promo code information for CPP that will be necessary to join Ledger Line data to CPP promotion data. It is equivalent to public.credit_ledger_line_refence.value in LEGACY.

columns.name: vendor
columns.description:
Contains the ID of the Identity Vendor used to process this Verification attempt.

0 = FanDuel

1 = Idology US

2 = Idology Canada

3 = Lexis Nexis

4 = Aristotle

5 = GAN

6 = ID Scan

7 = Aristotle Canada
